@msumit -> if the "serve logs" command is really not used anywhere, then I think @mik-laj  is right - we should remove it. The valid problem we solve this way is "we have to maintain this code even if it's not used so let's remove it".

Removing unused code is one of the best things an engineer can do to improve the project's quality. It increases test coverage, makes the code more maintainable, smaller, easier to refactor.

Code is usually liability not an asset.
